## RGB Color Mixer

Interactive RGB color controller built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
Users can mix Red, Green, and Blue channels, view the live color preview, and copy RGB or HEX codes.

## Current Features
🎚️ Adjust Red, Green, and Blue channels individually
🎨 Live color preview updates in real time
🔄 Reset all values to default (0, 0, 0)
➕➖ Increment / Decrement color values using buttons
📋 Copy to clipboard functionality for RGB and HEX codes

## Upcoming Features
🖱️ Hold-to-Increment — hold the plus/minus button to change values continuously
💾 Add to Palette — save selected colors to a custom color palette
🕒 Color History — automatically track recently used colors
🎨 Integrated Color Picker — select colors visually from a gradient field
🌈 HSL Code Display — show color in HSL format alongside RGB and HEX
📱 Responsive Design — optimize layout for mobile and tablet screens

## Technical Goals
Use clean modular JavaScript (no frameworks)
Keep functions reusable and maintainable
Apply DRY (Don’t Repeat Yourself) principle in code refactoring
Store data (palette + history) using localStorage

## Project Roadmap
Milestone	Description	Status
